latestPosts.caption:
I never thought I’d be posting again anytime soon. But this one…this one’s for @littlemissmukherjee 

A little context:
What do you do when every day folds into the next like a shadow with no edge? When the sun rises and sets but you feel nothing?

What do you do when brushing your teeth becomes the day’s greatest victory. When every “I’m okay” is a rehearsed lie so no one panics. When life feels like a broken record…same room, same walls, same aching stillness.

The paint starts peeling, not just off the walls, but off your soul. You notice it. You feel it. Too much and not at all, all at once. You want to scream, to run, to change something, anything but perpetually surrendering to this dull pain, but your body won’t move. Your mind won’t let you cause the world didn’t end when yours ended one random day!

what do you do then?

You turn to this girl, you turn to the light she brings in, and you hold onto it!

Yes, this is a gratitude post to her, she who saved my life. Quite literally.

I love you 🧿❤️‍🩹
- s
